Governor Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom has sworn in four new commissioners into the State Executive Council and charged them to be diligent and contribute to the development of the state. The swearing-in ceremony was performed on Monday at the Banquet Hall, Government House, Uyo. Emmanuel urged the newly-sworn in commissioners to shun self aggrandisement and work always in the interest of the Akwa Ibom people who they swore to serve. He also advised them not to be deterred by criticisms from different quarters. The governor urged them to bring to bear their wealth of experience as expressed on their resum√® towards the success of the Completion Agenda. Emmanuel also sworn in five new permanent secretaries. Those sworn-in as commissioners were Mr Uko Udom, Dr John James Edet, Mrs Idongesit Etiebet and Pastor Umo Eno. And the five permanent secretaries are Mr Ini Ikie, Dr Ini Etukudo, Mrs Esther Inyang, Mrs Grace Jim and Mrs Abasiekeme Essien. [NAN] Vanguard News Nigeria GOVERNOR Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom State has sworn-in four commissioners and a Special Adviser into office with a minor cabinet reshuffle. September 29, 2018 In "News" GOVERNOR Udom Emmanuel of Akwa Ibom State has inaugurated a five-man committee to verify and compile all projects executed in the state since the inception of his administration. May 16, 2019 In "News" Media aides to Akwa Ibom State Governor, Mr. Udom Emmanuel urged broadcast journalists in the state to strive towards attaining objectivity while serving information on issues to the general public. July 2, 2016 In "News"